items.title: Credit Suisse to pay $511 million for helping U.S. taxpayers hide over $4 billion overseas
items.description: "Credit Suisse AG committed new crimes and breached its May 2014 plea agreement," the DOJ said in announcing the penalty with the UBS subsidiary.

items.title: Federal judge says results of North Carolina court race with Democrat ahead must be certified
items.description: More than 5.5 million ballots were cast in what has been the country's last undecided race from the general election in November.

items.title: U.S. commodities regulator seeks to drop appeal of Kalshi election bets offers
items.description: Kalsi in January named Donald Trump Jr., the eldest son of President Trump, as a strategic advisor.

items.title: Trump, Jon Voight meeting led to Hollywood tariff proposal, his manager says
items.description: A White House spokesman said "no final decision on foreign film tariffs have been made," a day after President Trump's announcement of a tariff plan.
